==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trade name
<hw>Trade name</hw>. <sn>1.</sn> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The name by which an
article is called among traders, etc.; <as>as, tin spirits is a common
<ex>trade name</ex> in the dyeing industry for various solutions of tin
salts</as>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>An invented or arbitrary adopted
name given by a manufacturer or merchant to an article to distinguish it
as produced or sold by him.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The name or style under which a concern or firm does
business. This name becomes a part of the good will of a business; it is
not protected by the registration acts, but a qualified common-law
protection against its misuse exists, analogous to that existing in the
case of trade-marks.</def><-- now statutory protection? -->⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trade-off</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Tradeoff</ent>⟦br⟧
